transcription.text:
Speaker 1: I'm a current patient and I would like to cancel my subscription, sir.

Speaker 2: I'm sorry, what did you say your name was?

Speaker 1: Logan.

Speaker 2: Chicago.

Speaker 1: Gotcha.

Speaker 2: And Cal State California, correct?

Speaker 1: Correct.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Okay, it does look like you are a VIP member here.

Speaker 2: I'm assuming you're just still overstocked from the last couple months.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I'm a little overstocked.

Speaker 2: Yeah, okay.

Speaker 1: If you want, typically what our guys do here that are on the VIP status,

Speaker 2: they'll put themselves on like a once or twice a year setting for the refill.

Speaker 1: That way it does not come as often as every three months.

Speaker 2: It would be once or twice a year.

Speaker 1: So I could pause everything from now until August.

Speaker 2: We'd be the only one that you get charged for for the rest of the year,

Speaker 1: or until you call and let us know that you need it.

Speaker 2: Just an option.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: I mean, would I still be a VIP status if I could just call at any time?

Speaker 1: Like let's say I wanted to call in October, would I still get the same VIP status?

Speaker 2: Like if we cancel everything, no.

Speaker 1: And then the price might change as well.

Speaker 2: My understanding is because if we cancel everything, it cancels the prescription.

Speaker 1: And that's the most important thing to ordering the medication for the Viagra,

Speaker 2: if that makes sense.

Speaker 1: So, I mean, I could pause everything from now until August 24th.

Speaker 2: I don't know if you want to write that date down.

Speaker 1: I have everybody do that and then call in before then

Speaker 2: and then let us know when it's needed and not needed.

Speaker 1: We're very customer service friendly.

Speaker 2: As long as you work with us, we'll work with you.

Speaker 1: Gotcha.

Speaker 2: No, I'll do that for now.

Speaker 1: Sounds good.

Speaker 2: August 24th, if you ever want me again, my name is Charles, and it's 0040.

Speaker 1: Okay, cool.

Speaker 2: All right, sounds good.

Speaker 1: I hope to hear from you sooner than August.

Speaker 2: Other than that, I hope you have a great rest of your day, okay?

Speaker 1: I appreciate that.

Speaker 2: What's the current shipment when it comes in August?

Speaker 1: Or the amount of pills and what the price would be?

Speaker 2: Yeah, so you actually have options with that too.

Speaker 1: If it's 40 pills for $163.95, it would lock in for that price always.

Speaker 2: Or you can drop it down to 25 pills at a time for $99

Speaker 1: or 10 pills at a time for $49.

Speaker 2: Gotcha.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: Well, I'll just keep it at the current rate right now,

Speaker 1: at 40 pills, and I'll just call you guys before August 24th, you said?

Speaker 2: Yes, sir.

Speaker 1: Okay, cool.

Speaker 2: Yeah, that works.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: Sounds good.

Speaker 1: All right, Logan, hope you have a great day.

Speaker 2: Take care, brother.

Speaker 1: You too, Charles.

Speaker 2: I'll see you later.

Speaker 1: All right.
